OL,3,C2024 'almost certain' to be hottest
OL,4,Cyear on record
OL,6,FSamantha Burgess, deputy director of
OL,7,Fthe Copernicus Climate Change Service
OL,8,F(C3S) said: "After 10 months of 2024
OL,9,Fit is now virtually certain that 2024
OL,10,Fwill be the warmest year on record and
OL,11,Fthe first year of more than 1.5C above
OL,12,Fpre-industrial levels according to the
OL,13,FERA5 dataset.
OL,15,F"This marks a new milestone in global
OL,16,Ftemperature records and should serve
OL,17,Fas a catalyst to raise ambition for
OL,18,Fthe upcoming climate change
OL,19,Fconference, Cop29."
