OL,3,C2024 'almost certain' to be hottest
OL,4,Cyear on record
OL,6,FAs Cop29 begins next week, the World
OL,7,FMeteorological Organisation (WMO) is
OL,8,Fdue to publish an overarching analysis
OL,9,Fof global temperatures in 2024,
OL,10,Fdrawing on a series of datasets
OL,11,Fincluding the ERA5 data.
OL,13,FResponding to the figures, Mike
OL,14,FChilds, head of science, policy and
OL,15,Fresearch at Friends of the Earth,
OL,16,Fsaid: "The time for dither and delay
OL,17,Fis long gone. We need global leaders
OL,18,Fto smash the emergency glass now and
OL,19,Fdo everything in their power to
OL,20,Fprevent further harm."
